{"word":"ὑγρότης","slug":"ὑγρότης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὑγρότης</b></el> <el>(ὑγρότης, ητος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὑγρός'><el>ὑγρός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>wetness, moisture</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>pliancy, suppleness</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: of a flame, <i>flickering motion, lambency</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>languor</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}